A senior Palestinian police officer told Xinhua that everything could happen in the territories today or tomorrow because the Palestinians do not have their independent state in the territories on the historic date.The United States, seeking to persuade the Palestinians not to declare a state, urged on Monday again Israel and the Palestinian National Authority  not to take unilateral actions but set themselves a new target of agreeing on a permanent settlement within in a year.  GAZA CITY, April 27   Palestinian leader Yaser Arafat said here Tuesday that he favored to declare an independent Palestinian state on May 4 this year.The signing ceremony was planned at White House later Friday.This came in a statement issued by the Arab Parliamentary Union in the Syrian capital today.The latest round of war of words came at a time when the IsraeliPalestinian peace process is deeply deadlocked over Israel's prolonged delay in carrying out further troop redeployment in the West Bank.  JERUSALEM, October 23   Israeli former Prime Minister Shimon Peres expressed Friday welcome to the peace agreement reached by Israeli and Palestinian leaders at Wye Plantation outside Washington.  CAIRO, June 28   Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa reaffirmed Sunday that Egypt opposes Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin's proposal for holding a Madrid II international conference on the Mideast peace process.U.S. President Bill Clinton on Monday officially sent a letter to Arafat, in which he once again asked Arafat to cancel the announcement of a state on May 4 and stressed the U.S. would help move the peace process forward after Israel's May 17 elections.Egypt interpreted the Netanyahu proposal as an attempt to annul the landforpeace principle set by the Madrid conference and the Oslo accords that Israel signed with the Palestinians.